cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for predicting continuous real values by integrating multiple data sources and aggregating the results of different ML algorithms. The paper also introduces the concept of an Artificial Continuous Prediction Market (ACPM) to address the prediction of real values. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Q-learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and the application of ACPM to a specific data set, which falls under the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology).
